The article discusses the Los Angeles Declaration on Migration and Protection, presented by President Biden at the Summit of the Americas. The Declaration aims to transform the approach to managing migration in the Americas and is organized around four key pillars: stability and assistance for communities, expansion of legal pathways, humane migration management, and coordinated emergency response. The article emphasizes the need for economic stabilization and support in countries housing millions of refugees and migrants. It also highlights the importance of expanding legal pathways for protection and opportunity, as well as securing borders with humane policies to reduce irregular migration. The focus is on humane border enforcement, facilitating returns, and strengthening law enforcement cooperation to combat smuggling and trafficking.